two-point correlation are developed. Starting from a pair of root structures,
which are not related by translation, phase inversion or axis reflections,
child structures of arbitrary resolution (i.e., pixel or voxel numbers) and
number of phases (i.e., material phases/species) can be generated by means of
trivial embedding based phase extension, application of kernels and/or phase
coalescence, such that the generated structures inherit the
