assumptions of end-to-end learning regimes hinder the use of neural networks on
large application-grade datasets. This work addresses the assumption that
output class-labels are defined for all classes in the domain. The amount of
data collected by modern-day sensors span over an incomprehensible range of
potential classes. Therefore, we propose a new learning regime where only some,
but not all, classes of the training data are of interest to the classification
